<|startoftext|>Question:How long do i have to pay?
Answer:Depends on what company the company (e.g. AOL) is.  Most companies are looking for more than a day, depending on your age and ability or the number of hours work he can work at a time.  Most of them will let you sign a contract and that person will have an agreement upon the termination of their contract that includes the termination of the contract with the company and the time they would have to work out a termination agreement.  

If you have more than 40 hours of work as a contract employee, then you can do it before you decide.  

I went through this many times in my career and thought that if I waited to have my pay increase the only thing i could really do was take the contract and sign it off that way.  Not really.  I think it's more about the experience you have, and that you'll only do it if it's an emergency.<|endoftext|>
